  </property>
  <property name="windowTitle">
   <string>Form</string>
  </property>
  <layout class="QVBoxLayout" name="verticalLayout">
   <item>
    <widget class="QLabel" name="widget">
     <property name="text">
      <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;Permittivity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Computes the complex permittivity ε* = ε′ − jε″ of a material from its measured S11 (frequency domain, e.g. an open-ended coaxial probe immersed in a liquid), using the bilinear (3-standard) calibration method.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At every frequency the S11 → ε* map is a bilinear transformation fixed by three coefficients, which are recovered from three calibration standards with known permittivity: open (air), water and saltwater. The three standard measurements are loaded from touchstone files configured on this operation; the standards' known ε* comes either from the permittivity columns of those files (custom format) or from built-in reference models (air = 1, water: Debye/Kaatze, saltwater 0.9% NaCl: Cole-Cole/Peyman) evaluated at the configured liquid temperature.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The output trace contains ε′ as the real part and ε″ as the (positive) imaginary part. Display the trace in &lt;span style=&quot; font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;Real&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span style=&quot; font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;Imaginary&lt;/span&gt; format to see both.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The result is only valid inside the frequency range covered by all three standard files; a warning indicates points outside of it or frequencies where the standards are too similar for a reliable calibration.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
     </property>
     <property name="wordWrap">
      <bool>true</bool>
     </property>
    </widget>
   </item>
   <item>
    <spacer name="verticalSpacer">
     <property name="orientation">
      <enum>Qt::Vertical</enum>
     </property>
     <property name="sizeHint" stdset="0">
      <size>
       <width>20</width>
       <height>40</height>
      </size>
     </property>
    </spacer>
   </item>
  </layout>
 </widget>
